definitions.definition: A sport involving the performance of sequences of movements requiring physical strength , flexibility , and kinesthetic awareness .
examples: Gymnastics was a significant part of the physical education curriculum.

definitions.definition: Complex intellectual or artistic exercises or feats of physical agility .
